d track' unbroken over several (in this case,\nfour) decades in $L_{\\rm X}$. Comparing the radio/X-ray spectral evolution(s)\nwith the $L_{\\rm R}$ -- $L_{\\rm X}$ plane, we find that the X-ray softening is\nconsistent with X-rays produced by Comptonization processes in a radiatively\ninefficient accretion flow. We generally disfavor X-ray emission originating\nsolely from within the jet, with the possible exception of X-rays produced via\nsynchrotron self-Compton processes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Dec 2020 20:03:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-17"}
