t host galaxy, but is a\nbackground object in the redshift range $0.247 < z < 0.5$. The intervening\nspiral galaxy at $z = 0.247$ provides a natural host for the putative lens\nresponsible for symmetric achromatic variability and is shown to be a Seyfert 2\ngalaxy. We also show that, as for the radio emission, a \"multizone\" model is\nneeded to account for the high-energy emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Dec 2020 20:39:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-10"}
