eatflow\nfor roughly ten solar system lifetimes. Hydrogen-water demixing could slow\nNeptune's cooling rate by an order of magnitude; different hydrogen-water\ndemixing states could account for the different heatflows of Uranus and\nNeptune.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Dec 2020 02:20:09 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 30 Jan 2021 23:35:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-02"}
