rces the SiO 2-1 line wing emission is either\nbelow our sensitivity limit or that the bulk of the SiO emission may be\nproduced by the expansion of an H{\\sc\\,ii} region or supernova remnant, which\nhas pushed molecular gas away forming a shock and yielding SiO.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 8 Dec 2020 11:03:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-24"}
